23 SUMMARY
2244 This bill repeals the laws governing the Natural Areas Program administered by the
2255 Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry and reassigns certain
2266 responsibilities under the program to the Department of Inland Fisheries and Wildlife. The
2277 bill updates relevant definitions in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 12 and
2288 cross-references in Titles 36 and 38 to reflect these changes. The bill also establishes the
2299 Natural Areas Conservation Fund, which is administered by the Commissioner of Inland
3300 Fisheries and Wildlife. It also replaces the coordinator of the Natural Areas Program with
3311 a person appointed by the commissioner who is responsible for monitoring natural areas.
